df_dummy = pd.get_dummies(df, columns=['genre'], drop_first = False, dtype=int)
In [24]:
df_dummy.columns
Out[24]:

       'jp_sales', 'other_sales', 'global_sales', 'genre_Action',
       'genre_Adventure', 'genre_Fighting', 'genre_Misc', 'genre_Platform',

       'genre_Simulation', 'genre_Sports', 'genre_Strategy'],

In [25]:
X = df_dummy[['genre_Action',
       'genre_Adventure', 'genre_Fighting', 'genre_Misc', 'genre_Platform',
       'genre_Puzzle', 'genre_Racing', 'genre_Role-Playing', 'genre_Shooter',
       'genre_Simulation', 'genre_Sports', 'genre_Strategy']]
Y = df_dummy['global_sales']
In [26]:
X_train, X_test, Y_train, Y_test = train_test_split(X,Y, test_size = 0.2)
In [27]:
X_train.shape, X_test.shape, Y_train.shape, Y_test.shape
Out[27]:
((13032, 12), (3259, 12), (13032,), (3259,))
In [28]:
reg = LinearRegression()
reg.fit(X_train, Y_train)
print(reg.score(X_test,Y_test))

0.012580104919685642
In [29]:
Y_pred = reg.predict(X_test)
In [30]:
mae1 = mean_absolute_error(Y_test, Y_pred).round(2)
mse1 = mean_squared_error(Y_test, Y_pred).round(2)
mape1 = ((np.mean(np.abs(Y_test-Y_pred)/Y_test) * 100)/len(df)).round(2)
rmse = np.sqrt(mse1)

print(f"MAE: {mae1}\n MSE:{mse1} \n MAPE:{mape1}%. \n RMSE: {rmse}")

MAE: 0.57
 MSE:2.08 
 MAPE:0.04%. 
 RMSE: 1.4422205101855958
